This is the '''list of Schedule I controlled substances''' in the United States as defined by the [[Controlled Substances Act]].<ref name="DOJ 1308.11">[[Title 21 of the Code of Federal Regulations|21 CFR]] [http://www.deadiversion.usdoj.gov/21cfr/cfr/1308/1308_11.htm 1308.11] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090827043725/http://www.deadiversion.usdoj.gov/21cfr/cfr/1308/1308_11.htm |date=2009-08-27 }} (CSA Sched I) with changes through {{USFR|77|64032}} (Oct 18, 2012). Retrieved September 6, 2013.</ref> The following findings are required for substances to be placed in this schedule:<ref>{{uscsub|21|812|b|1}} [[United States Code]] via [[Cornell University]]'s [[Legal Information Institute]]. Retrieved on 2007-10-02.</ref>
# The drug or other substance has a high potential for abuse.
# The drug or other substance has no current accepted medical use in treatment in the United States.
# There is a lack of accepted safety for use of the drug or other substance under medical supervision.

The complete list of Schedule I substances is as follows.<ref name="DOJ 1308.11"/> The [[Administrative Controlled Substances Code Number]] for each substance is included.

